animal.description:
Our precious GRACIE was discovered as a stray in Tipton County, TN, while running with a Great Pyrenees she met along the way. The owner of the Pyrenees discovered them and easily rescued his dog, but frightened Gracie ran into the woods and was not coming out to say hello. Before these kind people could get back with a trap to trap her, they found this precious dog had just been attacked by a large dog. At that point, Gracie gratefully accepted rescue and was taken to the Tipton County Animal Shelter where she was taken to a local veterinarian to be examined and treated for her wounds. Strangely, only one wound could be found. Thank goodness an angel was watching over her! Lee Riley, shelter director, walked Gracie by several large dogs at the shelter to check her reaction. Forgiving Gracie was non-reactive and showed no fear. 

We contacted Lee, with whom we have often worked, to express our interest in helping this sweet, sweet girl just as soon as her stray hold is up. Who could resist those big Beagle ears! So, we took Gracie, along with Lily from the same shelter and featured also on this site, and both went immediately to our vet in Olive Branch where Gracie was treated for elevated liver levels, as well as her wound. Our vet, also, could find only one wound from Gracie’s attack, which easily healed. Her liver levels are perfectly normal now, giving us the green light to go on and spay her last week and do her dentals. We are seeing such good progress, as her video shows, that our vet permitted her to go to a temporary foster in Memphis for the two week holidays. Her foster dad is the same kind young man who fostered our Archie Beagle through heartworm treatment. 

Estimated to be about 3 years old, Gracie’s present weight is about 23 pounds. The only applications we are accepting for Gracie at the present time are from families who are interested in fostering-to-adopt. Our Hayley is presently in such a home and doing great with her heartworm treatment. Her foster family tells us what a great bonding experience it is to be such an integral part of her journey to wellness. They LOVE her! We want the same for Gracie—to be able to go into a loving home with a loving family who would like to be a part of Gracie’s journey to wellness and her forever home.  If you think you are the right family for Gracie and are willing to foster-to-adopt her, please contact Diana at dmoore2003@bellsouth.net.  We are very interested in talking to you and meeting you.

We should tell you that our Beagles are VERY popular. If you think you may be interested in this beautiful Beagle girl, please write us for an adoption application to get your name on her potential adopters’ list, many of whom are willing to wait for our dog till all vetting is completed. Please ask to apply only if you are a serious adopter and plan on completing our adoption application. We are inundated during the pandemic with adoption application requests.

animal.description:
Apply to Adopt Me!

"Percy" Cole Prince Jackson

Do you wish you could come home every day and have someone super excited to see you? Do you need daily laughs in your life at the antics of a dog? Then you will love Percy Cole Prince Jackson and see why his foster mom has nicknamed him "Chocolate Kiss." Besides looking like a miniature chocolate lab, this dog is always super excited to see anyone and everyone, and he will greet you with all kinds of doggy kisses and wiggly butt - sometimes will even show off and run in circles and bounce when you enter a room. He is a super sweet 2-3 year old, 40-lb., possible lab/hound mix bundle of love. He has short chocolate brown shiny fur with some white patches on chest and paws, and golden eyes. He is great with all people and older kids, has not been tested with young children, but would likely be fine with some formal training to calm down and manner lessons. He lived the first years of his life outside but is a smart boy and learning his inside manners and is almost 100% housebroken. He is happy to curl up with his people after playtime and is a snuggler. When he came to our rescue from rural GA, he was a "light positive" for heart worms. He's been treated and will need follow up with our vet (at the rescue's expense) to make sure he's all clear. He's playful and energetic, and would do best with a dog(s) his size or bigger to rough and tumble with, or as an only dog. If he's an only dog, he needs an active family that will pay lots of attention to him with plenty of love, walks and play time. He has been tested with a cat and he just sniffed and wagged his tail. He is fully crate trained and will sleep quietly through the night and be ready to greet you in the morning with his chocolate kisses! We are requiring Percy's adopter to have a minimum 6-ft. secure fenced-in yard for him.
If you think you have the perfect forever home for Percy, we'd love to find out more about you. Please fill in our adoption application and we'll see if you're Percy's perfect match.

animal.description:
PLEASE read his entire bio and answer the questions at the end, we will not respond to you if you don't answer the questions. 
Our sweet Sarge is back, through no fault of anyone, his adopters were wonderful and took him to a behaviorist and after several sessions, it became clear he is a very reactive dog. Absolutely nothing mean or aggressive, he just has a hard time with a lot of activity going on around him. This is what's hard about stray dogs, we have no history and cannot predict every scenario. So his needs have changed, no young children (12yrs and younger), no cats and no dogs, he needs plenty of room to run, more than a large yard, he needs acreage. He needs some one who can give him a job, who would consider agility training for him, who has time for training. 
 
Sarge is an 5yr old German Shepard. Sarge came in as a stray with terrible skin infection from fleas, he was infested!!! He has lost a good portion of his fur, but its growing back. His skin still has along way to go, with medicine, a proper diet, dewormer and of course flea treatment we've already seen a difference. We can see he is feeling better as he runs around our backyard playing, chasing the balls, rolling in the grass and well just being a happy dog. He knows some commands and is a very loving, sweet dog. 

My adoption fee is $150

Please answer the following questions, so we know if you are a good fit for Roxy. All our dog meet and greets are by appointment only, we try to get back to everyone in 72hrs, multiple e-mails are not necessary and we cannot answer any questions over the phone. 

1. Do you own or rent? If you rent can you get a letter form landlord stating you can have a large dog? 
2. How many people live in the home? Age groups? 
3. Do you have a large fenced yard? Preferably acreage? 
4. Do you have cats or dogs? If so, please don't apply. Primary Color: Tan Secondary Color: Black Weight: 82lbs Age: 5yrs 2mths 3wks Animal has been Neutered

He is an extremely sweet and intelligent family dog. He loves kids and other dogs of all sizes. He hasn’t been tested around cats off the leash, but we really don’t think he would hurt a fly. 
He’s obsessed with tennis balls and playing fetch. He lives to please his people. He was found as a stray and is heart worm positive and in treatment. He can definitely stand to put on more weight but he has plenty of energy.

Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information.

animal.description: Meet Guero, star member of the 'Best in Ears Club'! Guero is a sweet guy who is a little overwhelmed about this shelter living business. In his evaluation, staff said he was nervous but tolerated other dogs greeting him and was friendly with the handlers. He gave good greetings and corrected appropriately when he needed space. He was a bit anxious but friendly and warms up quickly. Guero is not a fan of small dogs. Maybe he's worried about competition in the ears club? Whatever the reason, no small critters in his future home please! In one of Guero's previous homes he was kept outdoors and he let us know that he would really like to move on up into the nice warm (or air cooled) house he has been dreaming of. He did well with kids he knew but might need to take his time with meeting new ones. His family reported that he was housetrained. I met this sweet boy for the first time today. He was a bit shy but met me at the kennel door, leashed up well and was ready to go. He really enjoyed our walk, smelling all the smells. And his ears are fantastic! Can't wait to get to know him a little better. - PACC volunteer

If you have any questions please feel free to call us at 919-266-8177 or email pets4adoption@bellsouth.net. All adoption fees are cash or check only, we do not accept credit cards for adoption fees.

To speed up the adoption process please visit our webiste, www.mmahrescue.org, to fill out an application and get pre-approved when you arrive to meet your new best friend! Prior to meeting an adoptable animal we do require an approved application to be on file, sorry for this inconvenience.

Cat adoption fees are $50 for kittens under 16 weeks of age and $75 for kittens/cats over 16 weeks of age. Dog adoption fees are $150 for puppies under 16 weeks of age and $175 for dogs over 16 weeks of age.

animal.description:
Buster – A Handsome, Smart and Loyal German Shepherd
Sedona Shepherd Sanctuary is teaming up with Plainfield Humane Society to help save Buster, a handsome and friendly 7 year-old German Shepherd.  Buster is extremely intelligent and enjoys nothing more than to show off his obedience and retrieving skills.

Buster is a pure bred German Shepherd with all the expected good looks of the breed.  He has lived with a family most of his life.  Unfortunately, in the past year, Buster had two bite incidents and was surrendered to the shelter.  According to his owner, the first occurred over some food that he took off a table outside his house, and the second when he was startled while being asleep.

He has been at the shelter since October and has been on his best behavior.  When we met Buster, he allowed us to walk right into his play area.  He then immediately engaged us with a toy in his mouth ready to play.  Buster will easily drop items and allow you to take toys out of his mouth.  He is comfortable with handling and does not show any signs of aggression.  He can however guard food, although he did not do so when we performed a food temperament test on him.  Buster allowed us to pet him and place fake hand near his bowl without incident.

Because Buster has a bite history on him, the shelter is only able to place Buster through a rescue.  Sedona is looking for a foster to adopt situation.   We believe that Buster has the temperament and personality to thrive in a loving home, someone with experience with the breed.   When outside of his run, Buster has interacted nicely with other dogs and is possible he could go to a home with other dogs.

If you are an experienced owner willing to give Buster a second chance, please fill out our adoption form or shoot us an email at contact@sedonashepherd.com for additional information.

Please note:

Sedona Shepherd Sanctuary's mission is to rescue adult and senior German Shepherd and mixes and find them loving homes. All of our dogs are fully vetted, up to date on all their shots

Our adoption area includes New Jersey, Delaware Valley, Manhattan, Southern New York. We may adopt to Connecticut depending on circumstances. Please visit our website at www.sedonashepherd.com.

Sedona

animal.description:
Meet Ida!

12-year-old Ida entered the San Diego Humane Society-Escondido as a stray and wasn't claimed. Ida sure was a happy girl in the car on her Freedom Ride. She enjoyed looking out the window and then took a nap, no doubt dreaming of her new life as a Frosted Face! Soon after we picked up Ida, we addressed her severe dental disease. She had 26 teeth removed, the remaining teeth cleaned, and now her mouth feels so much better! Ida is a sweet and quiet girl who has poor vision and hearing. She appreciates being approached gently to get her attention.

Ida went to live in a wonderful foster home over the holidays, and she has really blossomed with the love, patience, and enriching activities offered by her foster family.

She's potty trained, crate trained, sleeps through the night, not aggressive or bitey, rides well in the car, and is calm around other dogs. When Ida first arrived at her foster home, she was a little skittish and unengaged, but she has been steadily opening up and showing her cute personality to her foster family. Just over a month later, she is starting to snuggle, standing on her hind legs for treats, romping in the yard, and having zoomies!

For dogs like Ida, who seems to be in the early stages of dementia or cognitive dysfuction, it is important to still provide mental stimulation. Her foster family takes her on outings and introduces her to new places, people, dogs, and experiences, including a snuffle mat! A snuffle mat encourages sniffing and foraging for food, and Ida really took to it! As you can see in the video, Ida

(red harness) had fun finding treats - and shared so nicely! - with her foster sister FF Macy (also looking for her forever home.)

Ida's foster mom shares, "Her foster dad and I love her, and we know she's the perfect match for someone, idiosyncrasies and all. We're just waiting for that special someone to come along and give her a chance to be the goofy, quiet, low maintenance, adorable companion we know her to be. We know Ida isn't for everyone, but she'll be everything to someone. If you think you're Ida's someone, we can't wait to meet you!"

Might you be Ida's special someone? If you think you might be, please apply to meet her:
www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/apply

Come visit our next Open House on Saturday & Sunday 10 AM - 1 PM.

Learn more about our programs at www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/family No adoption fees and we help with medical costs!

Questions: adopt@frostedfacesfoundation.org

Updated: 2/2/21 KG

animal.description:
Camo was surrendered after 6 years because his family was moving into a home with other dogs. He is not good with other dogs and has been like that since he was a young pup.  Camo is an affectionate, calm, 6 year old gentleman who loves nothing more than leaning in for attention and petting.

Although Camo enjoys a quick run in the yard, he is happier to take a long, brisk walk.  His leash manners are excellent, and he knows basic behavior cues.  He prefers human interaction to other animals, so he would be best as the only pet in the house. 

His owner stated that he was good with children and could become protective of them.  Camo would fit into a home that would take him for frequent walks and allow him to  lay at their feet and be loved.

Due to Covid, the shelter is has an appointment only policy. We ask potential adopters to fill out our application, prior to a scheduled meeting. The staff is very accommodating, and we welcome any inquires.

Sparky is a handsome male Labrador Retriever/Pit Bull mix who was surrendered by his owner on December 13, 2020 because he could not be trusted with a newborn infant in his home.  Sparky was adopted from HSOV in August 2017 and is approximately 8-9 years old at the present time.

Sparky has a white-and-black short smooth coat, a long tail, and an adorable (rather mischievous-looking face) with a large black patch around his right ear, a black button nose, and short semi-erect ears.  

His previous owner told us that Sparky was good with their older children (10-years+) but that he did not do well with their newborn infant (which is the reason he lost his home).  Sparky does NOT do well with other dogs or cats and should not go to a home with other animals.

Sparky is frightened of loud noises, vacuum cleaners, and water.  He usually seeks a more quiet place to get away from the noises or one where he feels safe.  

Sparky is a smart boy who knows several basic commands (sit, stay, down, and shake).  He tends to jump when he wants to give hugs :)   His favorite toys/activities are his purple dinosaur, rope toys, walks, snuggles, and taking naps.

Sparky has been kept indoors and is housebroken.  He enjoyed short walks each day with his family.

His owner wanted potential adopters to know that Sparky nips when he is excited, but that there is a big difference between his 'happy-to-see-you' nip and an actual bite.

Sparky is protective of his food but only shows aggression toward other animals who 'mess with his food bowl'.

Sparky weighs 68 lbs and is fairly strong/energetic on a leash.  He has already been neutered. Sparky would do best with an experienced handler (and a home where he could be an 'only child').

I am available for adoption; however due to my breed my adoption will have to be facilitated through a rescue organization. Please see the front desk staff or contact the Shelter at (248) 858-1070 for more information.

Meet Bella! Sweet girl, Bella is looking for a permanent residence to call her own! This young girl has a lot of life ahead of her and mountains of potential to be a wonderful new friend! Bella came from a home that she shared with another canine and they did very well together! Bella, like all pets, deserve to be in a loving, safe and secure home, with compassionate owners, willing to give her all the time she needs to adjust!

American Pit Bulls are a misunderstood breed; for this reason, we implore adopters to these beautiful dogs to be very vigilant in training and socialization. This breed is very energetic and will need daily exercise. Because of their strength and energy, apartment living may not be the best fit. This breed can be loving, loyal and very smart. 

The above behaviors and personality traits have been observed while at the Shelter. If this animal was relinquished, information is gathered from the owner regarding behavior. Our wonderful volunteers spend time with these animals and give input on behaviors and traits. However, this description may not be all inclusive to how this animal will act in a loving forever home. Introduction to established family pets should be slow and monitored always. The same goes for children and other family members. Adopting a pet is a big decision and should be thoughtful. We suggest researching different breeds to match traits and personalities to your lifestyle. When adopting a pet, please know that this pet will be with you for their lifetime; patience and consistency will make for a successful adoption.

animal.description: Maverick is a 4 1/2 year old boston terrier/australian shepherd mix, from what we were told. He is medium sized and weighed 33 pounds at his vet visit on 12/17/20. Maverick is shy and a bit fearful in new situations and with new people but he warms up within a few days.and then wants to be everywhere that you are. Maverick does not like small children, according to his previous owner and that was one reason that she had to surrender him. She ran a daycare and Maverick just didnt warm up to the loud noises and sudden movements that young children make. Maverick has no issues with other dogs and cats are unknown. Maverick does have a cherry eye, which you can see in his picture but vet says that it is mostly a cosmetic issue and that repairing it can sometimes cause dry eye it does not bother him and is a fairly small one. Overall, Maverick is a healthy boy. He would do best in a home with older,children and/or adults. People who can give him his space and the time to adjust to his new surroundings without forcing themselves on him. Maverick does walk on a leash but does pull some. He is pretty strong considering his size. Maverick also likes to ride and will jump right into the vehicle. He does not like his nails trimmed or getting a rectal temperature (he did have to be muzzled by the vet for both of these procedures). Maverick will do really well with someone who can be home with him most of the time. Mavericks adoption fee will be $175 and will help to cover his cost of care while with us. If interested in giving Maverick his forever home, please submit your interest and adoption application or text ONLY to (352)215-3260 (phone calls will not be returned or answered at this number) for more information.

animal.description:
Miss Chloe is around 4 years old and weighs in at h70 lbs. She is an English Bulldog mixed possibly with American Bully. CHLOE was dumped in the desert along with a male of similar breed and we think she was  possibly used for backyard breeding. She is SO sweet! This little girl just wants love, affection, and guidance. We don’t believe Chloe was ever someone’s “pet.” She came to us knowing few manners or basic commands,  but she is quickly progressing. 
She is a fast learner and eager to please. Chloe would probably do best in a home with a submissive/playful dog. She likes to play with our Chihuahua and other more  “aloof”-type dogs. Chloe is still learning some manners and is a little mouthy. We think she would probably do best in a home with older kids. She’s a morning girl, waking up energetic and eager to play,  but her energy bursts are short-lived. Chloe hangs out contently in her kennel until it’s time to come out and play again. If you think you can provide beautiful Chloe with her FOREVER home, please contact us. To get more information on a Pups On Parole dog, please contact a representative of the Lassen Humane Society at 530 251-7247 or e-mail ilovepopdogs@yahoo.com.  The Pups On Parole Program started in June of 2007 to help give homeless dogs a second chance at finding an adoptive family.  All dogs in the program spent time in our local county shelter, surrendered by their owners or picked up as strays and waiting for their owners to redeem them or to be adopted by new families.   The selected dogs are brought current on vaccinations, spayed/neutered if necessary, micro chipped, and heart worm tested.  They then are taken to the California Correctional Center Firehouse where they are assigned to a trainer/ inmate fire fighter.  These trainers groom and work with each dog and give them the extra time and attention they need to become wonderful family companions.   Most graduates are house trained and know basic obedience commands.  As of December 2018, 535 dogs have been adopted through this program.  To meet any of the Pups On Parole dogs, arrangements must be made in advance.

Meet Lady... This sweet girl was owner surrendered to the shelter with her Mom Bella. Bella appears to be a schnauzer mix but we have no idea what Lady’s dad is. Lady is around 2 years old and 25 lbs. Lady is sweet but very timid at first with new people and situations. She needs you to take it a little slower at first and let her come around at her own speed. Due to her being timid at first we don’t recommend her for a home with small children or one out of the area where she would have to go on transport. Once settled she attaches to her person and is a complete Velcro dog. She does well on a leash and really is a good girl. She’s playful and active. Lady is utd, hw neg (tested below detectable levels) and spayed!

animal.description:
ALL adoptions require a completed application, vet check, home check and final contract.  The application to adopt can be found at www.camorescue.com.

Gus is a sweet senior guy that just wants a lap and love.  He loves to lay in his bed or on the sofa with you. He is about 13.5 years old.  Gus weighs 12 pounds.  He is potty and crate trained.  He is fine with grooming. He lost quite a few teeth and needs to be on canned food.  He is good with other small dogs and cats.  Due to some vision and hearing loss, he is not recommended for a home with small, active kids or dogs as he just wants to chill in his old age.   

He is available at the end of January unless you can get him to his vet in Conroe for his last vet appt. 
 He is neutered, up to date on shots, hw negative, microchipped and just had a dental. 

Adoption fees are variable. Up to date vaccines, microchip, spay/neuter are included in the fee.

Once your application has been approved, we will put you in touch with the foster to set up a  meet and greet. We are a foster based RESCUE, not a shelter. All of our dogs are in individual foster homes. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We select the best applicant for each dog, based on the dog's needs. 
For the safety of our small breed dogs and based on our past experiences, we will not place our dogs in homes with large breed dogs.    

CAMO rescue is a 501c3 whose primary focus is rescuing small dogs from the euthanasia list from high kill TX shelters.   
EIN # is 46-5486022
We rescue 800+ animals a year.

Follow us on Facebook at www.facebook.com/camorescue

Our donation link is http://www.paypalme/camorescue 

We are strictly volunteer based, no salaries are paid and 100% of donations go towards rescuing dogs.

** Courtesy Post **
Meet Finnley! Finnley, aka Finn, is a very handsome dog who was rescued from the streets of Puerto Rico. He learned to survive on his own. He is fearless, has a big personality, can be willful and strong headed, but is very willing to please. This just means he needs a dog savvy, experienced leader. He is now ready to find his perfect family!

Finn is about 3 years old and well trained!  He has a high energy level and high drive that requires an active family/owner with lots of exercise and structure. Finnley has been socialized around other dogs, but can be dog selective at times, so he will do best as an only dog.  His ideal home will provide lots of exercise and structure. NO kids please. He was failed by a rescue that brought him North and placed him in an unsuitable home where he was not allowed any time to decompress and pre-teen kids in the home teased him and were unkind to him. Due to his past traumas & unkind treatment Finnley cannot be dealt with in a harsh/forceful manner, but rather needs someone who is calm, patient, consistent and confident.

Finnley is a great best friend & active companion for the right dog lover.

Want to meet Finn? Email us at Josierescuefriends@yahoo.com

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Healthy adult maleTaz is a really good companion dog. He listens very well, knows commands and loves people he knows. It takes him a little bit before he warms up to new people - but it happens quickly. He does not bite a human - he gives a ferocious bark - good for strangers. He is barrier frustrated so it would be good for him to have a wooden fence if kept in the backyard for long periods of time. He absolutely loves human affection and touch. He is very playful.

He needs a strong person to be his leader. He is not good with other dogs, however. He will break off if commanded and can be redirected easily before engagement - but he needs an experienced dog handler for his new owner.

Please come visit Taz and check him out - He is a mighty handsome Boy.

All dogs and puppies are fully wormed, receive rabies and core vaccinations, microchipped, behavior assessed with other dogs and humans (sorry, no cat testing is done here), spend a minimum of 3 weeks free-ranging within a pack of 30 dogs to grow confidence and trust and may have DNA results. All dogs receive lifetime behavior support and can be returned anytime without a fee. 

PLEASE NOTE: You MUST complete an adoption application in order to see or adopt a dog from us. The completed adoption application ensures your 'spot' in order of adoption. Emailing/calling with questions will delay your adoption process.

ADOPTION APPLICATION --> www.petsreturnhome.org/adoption-application

animal.description: Thompson is a sweet 9 year old cocker boy whose had a rough life but we will be changing that for him STARTING NOW! Thompson gets along great with everyone and is happiest just taking in all the activities of his four legged friends. He could stand to lose a few pounds and his eyesight isn't the best but he will still be first at the kitchen table and for petting and snuggle time....his slow shuffle has turned into a confident trot and we are looking forward to seeing this  boy going from a "shut down shelter rescue" to a confident and loved member of someone's family. If you are interested in adopting Thompson please fill out an application at www.floridacockerrescue.org. Thompson is still being treated for some medical issues so we will do a foster-to-adopt situation for the right family- in this way Thompson gets to be in a loving home and we pay for his medical care until he is medically cleared.   ADOPTION FEE: $200.00

animal.description:
Meet Jina & Kaci. These girls were surrender to the shelter after their owner passed away and they were found laying on top. ? Jina and Kaci are senior girls and they are bonded. They will look for each other when not together. Jina is a teeny tiny 4 lb long haired chi. She is missing her bottom jaw but eats just fine. Kaci is a pretty Shih Tzu who is around 9 lbs. She does have cataracts and limited vision. She gets around good though considering. She started limping this week and we discovered she has luxating  patella. She has been started on meds and we will see how she recovers. Both girls are extremely friendly and loving. They are good with other animals. They will sleep in the bed with you or in a doggy bed. They are utd, hw neg (tested below detectable levels) and will be spayed before placement. We are ONLY looking for a home together at this point. If you can provide these sweet girls the perfect home to spend their golden years please fill out the app below. 

All dogs have a $175 adoption fee which includes vet check, age appropriate shots (atleast 2 sets for puppies), dewormer, heartworm test (if over 6 months), rabies (if atleast 16 weeks) and spay/neuter!

Puppies/Dogs that are not available for adoption due to vetting not being complete can be reserved with an approved application and a non refundable $50 deposit. This deposit is applied to your adoption fee and the remaining $125 is due at pick up.

Wags and Whiskers is an all-volunteer rescue. We also have full-time jobs and Families. We will try to answer all questions and applications in a timely manner. Please be patient and bear with us . Do not contact Parkway Animal Hospital as they are a vet clinic and can not answer questions on behalf of Wags and Whiskers. All questions and comments must go directly through the rescue. Thank you for your understanding.

animal.description: Stark is a one year old lab/retriever mix.  Stark is a very sweet boy but sometimes can play rough.  Stark will need someone who can understand his behaviors and also someone who understands his energy level.  He play bites and nibbles and sometimes can get into it with other dogs due to his playfulness and excited state.  He needs a family who is active.  If the family has another dog, a meeting with that other dog will be required.  It is best the other dog be laid back and not be alpha.  Stark could probably benefit from an obedience class.  He is very smart and loves to play.  Stark is neutered, microchipped, and up to date on his vaccinations.  If you are interested in Stark, please go to http://www.sparkyrescue.com/adopting and fill out an application.

animal.description:
Hans Gruber knows that there are two types of people in this world.
Those who think Die Hard is a Christmas movie and those who are wrong.

This adorable thief may be everyone’s favorite holiday villain, but this year the only thing he’s making off with is our hearts. Hans is a sweet 5-year-old Pit Bull Mix, who will make an incredibly loyal companion. He is affectionate by nature, loves hugs, and will blindside you with sloppy kiss when you least expect it. Hans is potty trained and knows some of his basic commands. We are unsure how he would do in a home with other dogs or cats. 

Hans Gruber is the perfect holiday treat! He can’t wait to bust out of Nakatomi Plaza and come hold your heart hostage for 600 million kisses! Find out more about Hans Gruber by filling out an application on our website www.streettails.org!

Hi! My name is Camry. My caretakers at RCHS would describe me as being in the ORANGE category. ORANGE– Dogs in the ORANGE category are commonly timid and will need some confidence building at first. Once dogs in the ORANGE category are comfortable, they will most likely be energetic and needing similar guidance to dogs that are in the YELLOW category. Dogs in the ORANGE category sometimes benefit from another confident canine in the home.

Dogs are assigned to color categories using any previous owner notes, general handling, as well as staff and volunteer observations. As we continue to get to know the dogs and gather further insights into their personalities, colors may be adjusted accordingly.

Rancho Coastal Humane Society remains temporarily closed to the general public, but we have companion animals in our care that are ready for adoption BY APPOINTMENT ONLY, and our staff is ready to make that happen! animal.description: Handsome Remington came to PACC as a stray with some injuries and was more than happy to let our friendly clinic staff patch him up so he could get to feeling better. Now that he's on the mend, Remington has got plenty of pep in his step and is hoping to finish up his recovery in a home instead his kennel here at the shelter. Remington is a sweet boy who isn't letting the cone of shame get him down. Staffers tell us he's friendly and sweet and while he's a slow walker, he's easy to leash up and walks politely. We don't know a lot about Remington, but we're looking forward to learning more about him if he's around long enough for us to get to know him. A few things we're sure of are that this sweet boy likes pets and treats and would love to get out of the shelter and into a home. If Remington sounds like your type of guy, make an appointment to meet him today.

Jefferson is a gentle giant. He is an 80lb Boxer/Lab Mix. This sweet boy may be very timid when you meet him, but once you gain his trust he is quite gregarious. Always in search of attention, he will be by your side seeking approval.

As he’s exiting his decompression phase, he has spurts of energy that can be quelled with a good walk or a good chew toy. He loves a good squeak toy as well. He’s perfect on a leash or in a harness.

Jefferson has done well with his foster brother who is a senior dog, and would do well in a home without an alpha dog. He’s calm and sleeps most of the day with his foster brother - and they enjoy their walks together.

If you would like to adopt Jefferson please fill out an adoption application at the below link:

animal.description: Hiya! My name's Leilani, and I'm a HERO! I was found risking my life to flag down a human to rescue my little Pug friend. He got tangled up in some bushes and was stuck, so I ran back and forth across the road until a nice lady stopped to help. I went right up to her to let her know I was nice, then went back to the bushes. She didn't understand what I wanted or why I wouldn't go with her, so my Pug friend let out a little bark. Then the nice lady followed me and freed my friend! I immediately checked him over and gave them both tons of kisses since he was safe! The nice lady says I'm "truly amazing" and "beyond friendly." She's pretty awesome, too! Even though I loved my friend, I'd prefer a home with no other pets. I want to be the star in your life! I am a very affectionate and energetic girl. I love attention, and am VERY loyal to my friends! With my happy-go-lucky attitude, I'm not afraid of strangers. They're just playmates I haven't met! I am crate trained, and won't destroy your things when you leave. I also know "sit," and am good with baths and nail trims. Your neighbors will like me, too, because I'm not very vocal. I'm so eager to find my forever home! Is it with you?? Fill out an application today so we can meet! ...

animal.description:
TECO is one of the electric company pups.  He wants to light up your life :)

With a guesstimated birthday in Dec. 2017, TECO weighs under 20 lb.  He's scheduled for neuter surgery the end of Dec. so should be ready in early January for God to send his forever family.

TECO is house-trained when taken out on a regular schedule - currently every 2 hours.  He is learning crate and leash manners.  He's affectionate and gets along with the other dogs in his pack.  

April 2020:  We are not holding public adoption events at this time.  Qualified families are being invited to appointments to meet specific dogs.  There are currently no opportunities to view multiple dogs and adoption events aren't being held at Tractor Supply in Lenoir.

Whether dogs / puppies come in as strays or owner surrenders, we usually have to make our best guess as to birthdate and breed.   

If adopted into a home with other animals, particularly cats, your new pet should be crated or secured when you're not available to supervise to insure a harmonious relationship.  

A vet reference is required to confirm responsible pet ownership.  We suggest first time pet owners look for an adult dog for companionship and to gain experience through another rescue or your local government-run animal control..

Adoption fee covers two vaccinations plus spay / neuter if using our local low-cost spay/neuter clinic (overnight stay required) and surgery occurs as agreed upon in the adoption contract.  Convenience fee equal to refundable spay/neuter deposit may be added if using our veterinarian.  Additional fees for 3rd puppy vaccination, refundable spay/neuter deposit, etc. may apply.  

We are an all-volunteer, foster-based rescue.  We receive no funding from agencies.  Available animals can be seen most Saturdays at Tractor Supply in Lenoir from 10:00 a.m. to 2:00 p.m.  We recommend interested parties contact us to pre-qualify for adoption so their new furry family can go home once paperwork is complete.  Fees are required in cash.  For more information on our organization, our website is www.petpartnersrescue.org.

animal.description:
Hello! Have you ever seen a dog as adorable as me?! Can you believe I’m homeless and am waiting for a wonderful person or family to adopt me? Great dogs like me end up in animal shelters every day- I know, it’s so hard to believe but it’s true!

My name is Colby and I just joined the adoptable doggy crew at Providence Animal Center from the sunny state of Florida. I'm around 7 years old, about 42 pounds, and I'm all set to move right into your heart & home today - already neutered, microchipped & up to date on vaccinations. 

The staff would love to match you with your new best friend forever - and hopefully that's me! I have been enjoying the scenic grounds here at PAC as well as socializing with my fellow dogs. Even at 7 years old, I am a bouncy and playful gentleman. I enjoy pets and cuddles from the staff and volunteers (check out my photos!). I get to go on car rides. I'm a great passenger -- not to brag. I have the best time exploring and hiking the nearby trails.

The staff thinks my ideal home would be with humans who are 18 & older. While I am friendly with some special dog pals here at PAC, I would prefer to be the only dog in the home. You see, I like to be spoiled and get all the attention. I did well on my cat test, so I could live with a cat roommate with a slow introduction!

What do you say? Can we be best buds? Please complete an adoption profile (found here - https://providenceac.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Adoption-Profile.pdf) and email to my contact at PAC at cmuller@providenceac.org. My people will be in touch!

Tail wags and smiles,

Colby

P.S. Someone is so excited for me to find my fur-ever home, that they have sponsored my adoption fee! That means I can join your family today for FREE! Woohoo!!

-------
During your appointment, you will be able to meet a selection of pets in the Kennels or Cattery that day. New pets are arriving daily!
-------

Providence Animal Center relies on adoption fees and donations to save pets! Adoption fees vary per pet. To find out this pet’s adoption fee or for more information, please call the Adoption Center with this pet’s ID number.

Can’t adopt? Consider fostering or donating! Visit https://providenceac.org/support-us/ for more information on how you can support the lifesaving mission!

animal.description:
** PLEASE READ DESCRIPTION FULLY BEFORE APPLYING THROUGH OUR WEBSITE BIGLOVEANIMALRESCUE.ORG **

Winnie is incredibly special to us! We rescued this 9-year-young senior boy from the streets after reports came in of his owner passing away suddenly. He was living in this cardboard box, with fleas, ticks, skin infections, and teeth rotting so bad, he could barely eat. We immediately got his skin treated, many of his teeth pulled and his skin, eyes and ears looked at and cleared up. Winnie is a beautiful poodle mix who is beyond precious, so sweet and ready for the next amazing phase of his life. His foster mom says he loves to sleep on pillows, loves to go on walks and of course loves to be loved and paid attention to. He definitely needs a forever home with a parent who works from home (pre-COVID) or is retired and will give a lot of love to Winnie. Though Winnie is good with other calm, older dogs, he prefers all the love and attention to himself.

Our adoption fee for all dogs is $500 and is tax deductible as we are a 501(c)(3) rescue. Our rescue also includes a microchip and keeps vaccinations up to date.

If you're interested in Winnie, you must visit our website and fill out an application here: https://bigloveanimalrescue.org/adoption-application-form/

**No meet and greets prior to approved application.

**Due to the volume of messages we receive on all of our platforms, we do not send follow up emails to our applicants and we do not read or reply to messages via PetFinder. We’re a small, volunteer ran rescue so we can only do so much in 24 hours. Thank you for understanding!

Again, please no repeat emails. If we feel you're the right fit, we will contact you.

www.bigloveanimalrescue.org

animal.description:
Apollo
Great Dane mix
Five years old, 54 pounds, 
Neutered, fully vaccinated, hw negative and microchipped. 

Looking for the ultimate cuddle bug?

This handsome guy is Apollo (5-years-old), and what brings him the most joy in life is laying beside - or often on - you on the couch. He's the perfect mixture of couch potato snuggle bug and playful tug-of-war champion.

When Apollo is really happy, he gives you a grin, wiggles around, and sneezes. He just can't contain his excitement!

Apollo is a bit reserved and appreciates, at least for now while he gets comfortable again, meeting people with slow introductions. A couple sniffs to make sure you're okay, and he's ready for some pets. This big boy is smarter than he lets on but is still nervous about his outdoor surroundings, so he needs a strong leader to keep up his training.

Apollo is a great house dog: house broken, crate trained (though he is fine to be loose in the house), distinguishes between toys and non-toys, and is careful to watch your fingers when you're playing. He does believe he's your sous chef, so don't be surprised if he shadows you in the kitchen! Also, Apollo would love a backyard so he can get out his zoomies and lounge in the sun.

Apollo would benefit from being an only animal so he can soak up all your love himself. Though he is fine with big dogs with proper introductions, he prefers to hang with humans. He may not be around small dogs or cats.  If you are interested in adopting Apollo, please email adoptsch@gmail.com or message the Second Chance Habitat Facebook page.

animal.description:
Name: Red Sonia
Age: 8 years old
Sex: Female/Spayed
Weight: 30 lbs.  working on weight loss
Coat: smooth
Color: red
Energy Level: low
Adoption Fee: $150
Contact: dmichael3399@gmail.com

Hello world, I'm Red Sonia!  You might notice that I'm a big girl.  I used to live with a kind gentleman that had dementia who loved me very much, and I loved him very much.  He would feed me ... and feed me again ... and feed me again .... and well, you get the picture.  I couldn't be rude, so of course I'd eat it all up!  My family decided that this just wasn't healthy for me, so they reached out to The Rescued Rescuers.  You see, I came into rescue at 30 lbs, and I should weigh half that, maybe less.  That's a lot of extra weight for my little frame to carry!  Foster mom has me on a diet (booo) and gentle walkies to help me lose some weight and then do brisker walkies.  I have a vet visit next week to get me all checked out and we didn't want to over-do things without getting me checked first.  Despite the diet (boooo) I'm doing well in my foster home.  I get along fine with the other pups. There's even crazy foster kittens running around, and I don't mind them either.  You might think that with me being a big girl, that I would be very food motivated.  Nope.  What makes me happiest in the world is attention from my humans.  Could you be that human that would be my forever home?  You would need to commit to continuing my weight loss and keeping me at a healthy weight.  But I would pay for that responsibility with total adoration!  

If you want to help with this dog’s medical expenses: 
https://therescuedrescuers.org/how-to-help

If you want to adopt this dog, apply at the link! 
https://therescuedrescuers.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
This sweet girl is Eudora. She originally came or us a few months ago when she was rescued from a hoarding situation with over 70 dogs!! All of her other pals have since been adopted and we don’t understand why this sweet girl hasn’t! Eudora has come a long ways since she was first rescued. She loves people of all ages!! She is so friendly and tries to sit as close to you as possible. During her stay with us, she has also played mother hen to several liters of puppies! She is so wonderful with them. Eudora has gained some weight since being rescued, maybe a little too much now. But this poor girl is realizing she doesn’t have to beat out 70 other dogs to eat. 

Like mentioned above, Eudora is as sweet as they come! While she is very friendly with people, she does have a few fears to still overcome. We have been working on getting her used to a leash and going on walks. That is still a work in progress. She is also getting used to car rides. Since that wasn’t anything she had every experienced before in her life, she does get a little car sick. We are hoping with some time and patience, she can learn to overcome that! 

Overall, Eudora is just a great girl who finally needs a home to call her own!

animal.description:
Fynn, 8 months old and 25 lbs., is a petite sweetheart of a Potcake (what Bahamians call local island strays) from Abaco, Bahamas. Fynn was found on the streets and raised in a local foster home for the past two months before finding his way to our organization in NY. He is currently in foster care in Fairfield, CT where he is slowly opening up to his human foster parents. He LOVES other dogs and will need a home outside of the city with another dog companion as this is where he finds his best confidence. His adopters should be patient and gentle and give him some time to trust and not be so shy/fearful. Fynn is not aggressive or reactive at all, he just needs a patient family to wait for him to open up. When he does, the love is incredible. A fenced in backyard is important for Fynn..

Please email elli@mrbonesandco.org with questions. To meet Fynn, please complete an adoption at www.mrbonesandco.org/adopt first. Fynn is neutered, vaccinated and microchipped. His adoption fee is $500.00. You can see all his social media posts under #AdoptFynnMBC

Thank you!

Sometimes the pets appear to be a particular breed(s) in the pictures we receive from our rescue partners and when they arrive we are surprised to see an entirely different breed(s) in person! If you choose to DNA test your adopted pet, test results may vary from company to company and our breed guess may not be reflected in those results as it is just that, our best guess. animal.description: Hi! My name is Rain! I was rescued by the wonderful people at Big Dog Ranch from a hoarding house in Puerto Rico before arriving here at the ranch. I have been very cautious since being here on the ranch but that is because I'm not quite used to my surroundings yet and I came from a very challenging environment. I like to play with other dogs but I can be selective with who I choose to engage with. I would definitely be happiest living in an adult-only home, but I may be able to live happily with a feline friend or two. I'd be a good fit for an experienced dog owner who can help me learn that it is ok to come out of my shell. While I am very cautious, I am open to interactions with new people. I would be an excellent apartment dog and would be perfectly happy living a quiet lifestyle with my new owners. I would benefit from further training, but I do appear to have some understanding of potty-training. I know that I would make an excellent cuddle buddy if you would just give me the chance to prove it to you!

Meet Frankie and Howie, bonded boys that MUST stay together!

FRANKIE is a 3-year old Beagle who is very affectionate and loves toys, carrying sticks in his mouth and running through the snow.

Frankie does not like to be left alone and can get anxious, although medication is helping him with that. His new family must have patience to help him feel secure. An ideal situation would be a household where someone is home most of the time.

HOWIE is an 8-year old Basset/Beagle (AKA BAGEL) who loves tracking scents in the yard and barking as he waddles with his nose to the ground. Howie is quite overweight, although he has been working hard at getting in shape. He is very loyal, but likes attention on his own terms and doesn't like to be disturbed while sleeping.

A home with older children or no children would be best.

Howie's new family must also be committed to continuing his new healthy lifestyle and helping him shed a few more pounds.

If you have room in your heart and home for this dynamic duo, please apply at http://newenglandbassethoundrescue.org/adoption-process/adoption-application/

animal.description:
We are looking for what feels like a needle in the haystack. If this sounds like you or someone you know, please spread the word so we can help find Dash his forever home. 

Dash is a 3 year old pit mix looking for his forever home. Dash had had a rough start to life but Is hopeful someone has room in their heart to give him his happily ever after he so deserves. Dash was from a hoarding case down south where the rescue closed and left 85 dogs and over 60 cats to fend for themselves. He spent almost a year there and was kept in an outdoor run. He had limited access to food and water, and no access to love. This shaped him, but didn't break him.

 Dash has started to make some progress in his foster home, but has a long way to go. Dash is looking for a home who either has experience in working with dogs with severe anxiety, or willingness to work with a specialist. Ongoing training will be a requirement for his adoption. animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Ace adores curling up on the couch, affording the 53-pound black beauty a paw-fect view of the activities inside his foster home. As the 1.5-year-old former stray grows accustomed to the feeling of safety and the knowledge that a human touch can be tender, he's allowed his foster mom to pet his head more often and leash him for the walks he now likes, never pulling and always walking beside her. Not only has he discovered the joys of taking treats and playing with toys but he thrives on playing outdoors with his canine foster sisters. While he knows no commands as yet, he sleeps in his crate and is housetrained to use a doggy door. With so much to learn and so much potential, what Ace needs now is a home, with patient adopters to earn his trust, educate him fully and ensure that he's well loved and well exercised fur-ever.

Animal Rescue of the Rockies believes that every pet should find a wonderful, caring home. To ensure each pet finds the best possible home, we ask that you fill out our Adoption Application so we can learn more about you and your household. We review each application we receive and will contact you within 48 hours. If your home sounds like a good match for you and the pet, the next step is to set up a "meet and greet." After meeting the pet, if you would like to proceed with adopting, we'll ask that you read and sign our Adoption Agreement and pay the adoption fee. Our adoption fees help cover the costs of saving more lives! A home visit will be scheduled within one week of your new pet going home with you.

The adoption fee for this pet is $300. Our adoption fee covers the following:

- Spay/Neuter, Microchip

- DAPP vaccinations as age appropriate for dog - adopter shall be responsible for all DAPP boosters after adoption.

- Rabies vaccinations as age appropriate for dog - adopter shall be responsible for any rabies vaccinations after adoption.

If you are interested in adopting, please fill out an adoption application by clicking here . We want our pets to go to a lifelong new home, so thank you for your patience during the adoption process!

Please email ARRColorado@gmail.com for more information, as we can not accept calls at this time. Our adoption process is:

1. Fill out our Adoption Application online. We'll contact you within 48 hours to answer any questions you may have about the pet.

2. If the pet looks like a great match, we'll schedule a meet and greet and ask you to fill out our online Adoption Agreement if you'd like to proceed with adopting. Once you've completed the Adoption Agreement and pay the pet's Adoption Fee, you can arrange to pick up your new furry family member!

animal.description:
Blitz is an 8-year-old Podengo who is just as sweet as it gets! He is in excellent health for his age and loves going for walks. He gets along well with other dogs that he has met but he really prefers females over males and especially other Podengos!
Blitz is not house-trained yet but is working on it. He is looking for a foster or adoptive home that is up for continuing his training. Blitz can be skittish in new situations and is a flight risk so a home where he will not get the opportunity to ever be outdoors without a leash is a must. He can easily climb fences and escape IF there is an opportunity to do so. He is a crafty guy! If you think you might be a good fit for Blitz, email us for more information about fostering to adopt at adopt@scituateanimalshelter.org 

All dogs are fixed, vaccinated, dewormed, flea treated and heartworm/lyme tested before adoption. Adoption fees are $360 for a dog, $460 for a puppy, and $250 for a dog with special needs or senior over 10 years old.

animal.description:
Zoey is a 7-year-old Great Dane/Basset mix who came to the Shelter because she was very protective of the women in her home. Zoey walks well on a leash, is house -trained, is in great health for her age, and tolerates calm dogs. Zoey doesn't like small animals like cats or rabbits and needs to be in a home without these critters. 

Zoey's new home should only have females in the home because she is very wary of men. If she is with a woman and a man is nearby, she will assume she needs to  protect the woman and will act aggressively towards the man. Without men around, Zoey is very calm and sweet. 

If you think you might be a good match for her, email us at adopt@scituateanimalshelter.org for more info on fostering or adopting this girl.

Olivia- Female/Spayed  Heeler Mix  Color: Chocolate & White 2 years old 40 lbs.
ID# D-39923
***Heartworm Positive***

Olivia was found on the street and brought to the shelter. She is a fun, playful sweet, active girl who appears to be housebroken. She will most likely make a great family pet, her finder says she was good with her kids and other dogs. She needs a secured fenced yard where she can have supervised exercise and playtime and the rest of the time spent indoors. She does need a little training to stop her from trying to bolt out a door, so something to keep in mind. She will make a great addition to your new pet family.

Olivia has tested POSITIVE for Heartworms. She has been started on daily medications for the slow kill method and her adopter will need to keep her maintained on monthly Heartworm prevention for the rest of her life.

Olivia is current on basic vaccinations including Bordetella, been dewormed and is microchipped. 

Olivia has now been spayed as of 12/17/20 and received her required Rabies vaccination. She is ready for her new home.

For more information, please contact the City of Corsicana Animal Shelter at (903) 654-4928. The shelter is open Mon, Tues, Thurs and Fri from 12:00pm - 6:00pm and on Sat from 12:00pm - 4:00pm.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Caramel is an American Staffordshire Terrier/Lab mix that just had his official first birthday with us on January 1! He is very friendly to people and curious enough to explore people, places, noises, and things when he's secure and loves to lean on his handler. So much fun! His adorable face means he gets away with more than he should!

THE GOOD:
knows basic commands sit, stay (for a moment), down (for jumping), has learned he's not allowed any counter, table, or food that basically smells the best. Loves being with his humans, so will not run away. Intelligent, friendly, playful, and would love to be a lap dog!

>>LEARNING:
greeting behavior (we discourage jumping), crate training (ok at night but does not like to be alone too long in the house), chewing dos and dont's, proper leash behavior (we use an extra long leash, the gentle leader, and a short leash for public outings). Proper pal play (too aggressive for most dogs so far)

>>FAVORITES:
walks are good but runs are better, fetch is ok, but tug of war is better, adults ok, but kids are better, cuddles and snuggles are best, but will take a lean or a paw on you until he is happy.

THE BAD:
needs a lot of oral stimulation. Loves any chew toy, but is just as happy to chew masks, socks, and dog beds. Not great at a dog park since he is an aggressive player. We're hopeful he'll learn manners soon. Can be a barker and/or a digger without enough stimulation.

THE UGLY:
Willing to make anything into a game, which makes discipline a challenge.

=========================================================

Please contact
app@aarfhouston.org
for more information about this dog. You can apply online by clicking on Application .

Puppies
that are under 4 months old cannot be adopted outside of our Veterinary Service area. Please call for specific locations.

Children under 8 years old
often are not a good match for our puppies and dogs. In order to protect both, your child and our rescued dogs/puppies from harm, we seldom if ever adopt to families with young children.

Once your application is approved, we will schedule a meet and greet at one of our adoption events. Thank you for considering a rescue!

The adoption fee includes vaccinations, Bordetella, de-worming, rabies, spay/neuter and microchip. There is a an additional $12.99 fee for Home Again for a lifetime registration of the microchip.
Puppies cannot be adopted outside of the Houston area until they are spay/neutered after they are 4 months old. It is against the law in the State of Texas for a rescue not to be sterilized so we have to make sure it gets completed and that we have record of it.
NOTE: In our bios, we provide information based on our volunteer's experience with a particular dog; such as temperament, training, and ability to get along with others.
AARF is a 501(c)3 Non Profit, all breed, no kill organization. Our group is always in need of donations in order to continue to give the needed medical care to our rescues. Adoption fees do not begin to cover all of the medical costs. Any donation , no matter how small is a big help and is greatly appreciated. Please help us to continue to help them. Thank you.

animal.description:
Just look into those beautiful eyes, and you will see that Willet WANTS to trust and love you. His anxiety about strangers, however, can make that a frustratingly slow process. Once he has accepted you, he is affectionate, playful, loyal, snuggly, and attention-seeking. He has good house manners, takes treats enthusiastically, and is always gentle. But it can take him several days to determine that a new person is familiar and trustworthy enough to let his guard down. When he encounters a newcomer in his home or on his property, Willet will bark intently, pacing and following the 'intruder,' staying close enough to keep an eye on him/her, but just out of arm's reach. Neither treats nor soothing words distract him. This makes him a great guard dog, but it's challenging for a home that gets visitors. Off home turf, Willet is more passive toward strangers but shows his overall fear by recoiling, trembling, and seeking to avoid any contact. In his foster home, he has started working on basic training to give him confidence and help him learn how to focus. Being just 2 years old, Willet is energetic and bouncy, enjoys playing with toys, and loves running around the yard, especially if there is a squirrel to chase. Willet would love to romp and play with his canine foster brother, but Robin isn't much of a player, especially since Willet, at 32 lbs., is more than twice Robin's size and often jostles and knocks him around. When Robin then gets testy about this, Willet just good-naturedly ignores him. Aside from some competitive marking in his first few days in foster care, Willet's house-training has been very good, and he uses the dog door like a pro. Willet is seeking a low-traffic household with understanding, dog-savvy humans, who are committed to positive training, so that he can continue his journey to being the best, most loyal companion ever. If that describes you and your home and if you feel drawn to helping Willet feel safe, check out his online album at https://imageevent.com/beales/fosters/willet . Be sure to read all the captions, where you can learn more details about this intriguing boy with the soulful eyes.
Our adoption fee is $175 for adult dogs or $225 for puppies under 6 months old.

If you are interested in adopting this dog,
PLEASE READ THE DETAILED ADOPTION PROCESS information on our website
at www.
NewRattitude.org/adopt/

From there, you can access our adoption application or contact our Adoption Team for more info.

animal.description:
Note: I require another canine companion within the household that will actively interact with me and 'show me the ropes'.

Hey everyone!!! I just got flown in from Puerto Rico. Let me tell you, that was a heck of a scary trip! 
    
My name is Canela. I’m 2 years old and 30lbs! I am here looking for a fantastic family to make me their forever dog. Let me tell you my list of wants in my forever family.....
    
I am very shy meeting new people so I need that special family that understands that it takes time for me to know I am at my forever home. I can be nippy when I get super scared but I come around with patience. I have good house manners once I get on a schedule and you pay attention to my cues.  I'm the kinda girl that once I feel I can trust my family I will do everything to please you. I walk good on a leash but all new things make me nervous. Just know I am working on that. I need a secure yard or walked on a leash. I LOVE other dogs, toys, and my foster family that is showing me the ropes. Lastly, I will do best in a dog experienced home. 
      
Don't pass me up cause I need more time than some dogs cause I definitely have as much love and personality as an outgoing dog. Remember to give me 3 days to settle in, 3 weeks to learn my routine, and 3 months to know I am yours forever!

What breed am I? Mixed mutt! ODHS does not breed label (unless there’s official paperwork), as studies show it is nearly impossible to tell the exact breed of each dog based off of their appearance.

Educational article:
3/3/3 rule:
https://www.rescuedogs101.com/bringing-new-dog-home-3-3-3-rule/?fbclid=IwAR2iv5m7fqk3FieO7LOsstGeGsYYV_F1rJOd1BPxaImofLpcinpYsUbFRWs

Adoption Donations are $250 for an adult, $350 for puppies (a dog under one year of age), and $125 for a senior dog (based on the age of the dog). Adoption donations are to be made via cash, and credit/debit card. There is a $5 fee to run cards.

Please remember to bring a collar and leash (non-retractable) with you the day of the adoption. Note: Martingale collars and slip leads are strongly recommended.

Due to COVID19, we aren't having as many open, public adoption events.  Current schedule is pre-determined meet and greet appointments are Wednesday evenings and on Saturday from 12-2.  
 Our adoption center is located at 3602 Lafayette Blvd, Suite 102, Fredericksburg, VA 22408. It's important that you keep an eye on your emails for any changes or updates during the adoption process.

Visit our website for an application to adopt. 
https://www.olddominionhumanesociety.org/adoption-application

Old Dominion Humane Society is a volunteer based organization. We are run completely by volunteers, who also have full time jobs, so we appreciate your patience.  Currently, the average timeframe for a response to your application is 1 week.

Like us on Facebook "Old Dominion Humane Society"
and be a part of promoting forever homes for dogs in need.
#Adopt #Donate #Foster #Volunteer 

Note: ODHS only adopts to Virginia and surrounding states (including D.C.). A $50 out of state fee applies.

animal.description:
Posie the Beagle here. Have you ever seen such long, lovely legs on a girl?! I am 4 years young and currently weigh about 17 pounds. I guess I didn't get enough to eat when I was a stray on the street so my foster mom is working on getting more weight on me.  I can run like the wind and jump too – so much fun! But I do require an escape-proof fence, at least 4' high. I need another dog in my new home, since I am a bit shy and would be the happiest girl ever to have someone to run and play with me – I have so much energy to share. My other life was not very good, as when I was a stray on the street,  I was found with a bullet wound through my chest that was badly infected. Thankfully, I was treated and rehabbed and you would never have guessed that happened. I am a bit jumpy around loud noises, but I’m sure you can understand that – those guns are really loud. I am so happy that I might find my own person as I am very affectionate and love to snuggle on the couch. I will be watching for applications so we can have so much fun playing in the yard with you and another friend.

All of our adoptable pets live with foster families in a family environment so we know their individual temperament and personality. This helps us to match the right dog with the right family to make sure everyone lives happily ever after.

If would like to adopt this dog, or another one of our dogs, please click on the application link on our home page to download our application. Please save the application to your computer and email it to Beagle911rescue@aol.com as an attachment.

If you would like to open your home to help other dogs in need, or you'd like to help with adoption events, walking dogs, etc., we are always looking for fosters and volunteers. If you are interested, please download our Foster or Volunteer application from our home page.

Nugget is an adorable little boy who came from the Valencia County Shelter where he was abandoned by his owners when they had to move and did not want to take him.  The shelter reached out to NMAF as soon as he arrived as the poor little guy was just terrified. He does not show interest in other dogs so would be fine as an only dog - perhaps as a companion for a still-active senior or couple.  He is sweet and easy to have around.  He will be neutered on December 17th and receive the rest of his medical requirements at that time so could be ready to go to his new home by Christmas.  In order to meet him, an application is required.  See details and link above.

Born 2018
Adoption Fee:  $195

NMAF ADOPTION APPLICATION, found at www.nmaf.org/adopt/adoption-application.

Please complete an Adoption Application if you are interested in Velvet.

Velvet, aptly named for her thick and velvety black coat, came to NMAF as a stray from a local rural shelter.  It only took one touch for her foster mom to give her the name Velvet, as her coat is soft, dense, and shiny.  The shelter had listed her as a Pomeranian mix, which is possible, but she is much larger (we estimate between 15 & 20 pounds) and long-legged.  Schipperkes, a Belgian breed, seem to match her better than Pomeranian, including her temperament, though there is definitely something else mixed in.  What a fun DNA experiment she will make!  Schipperkes are affectionate, smart (though not necessarily easy to train), and require regular exercise.  They are also good with children, though we have not had an opportunity to test that.  A better weight will be obtained when she is spayed and receives the rest of her medical requirements, including a heartworm test.  She is a self-possessed little girl, quiet and calm, and gets along with the other dogs in her foster home.  Cats are unknown.  She is well-mannered and easy to have around.  Once she is spayed, she may be ready to go to her Furrever Home by Christmas as long as she is kept quiet a few more days.  In order to meet her, an application is required.  See information & link above.

More Info:  Contact Kate at kmolsbe@gmail.com.

NMAF dogs cannot be adopted out of the greater Albuquerque / Santa Fe area.

Adoption Clinic Location:  PetSmart - Academy & Wyoming, Saturdays, 10:00 a.m. - 1:00 p.m. - Currently Suspended

Please visit our website at www.nmaf.org for more information.

animal.description:
After her life was spent, living outside in isolation and squalor, being used only as a breeding machine...She was rescued a little over a month ago, and gave birth to her last litter shortly after. 
Since then, she has struggled to adjust to life as a house dog...She desperately needs someone who will be patient with her and take the time to help her to heal from her traumatic past. On top of her mental anxieties, she is heartworm positive, and receiving treatment, so her exercise must be limited and she must have frequent vet appointments. Her spay is scheduled for December 18. 
She definitely seems to prefer the company of men over women at the moment. She is crate trained but obviously needs a spacious home and a large fenced in yard. 
She walks well on leash and does appreciate some attention and affection but she is still very very fearful of new experiences of any kind. 
Rosie will need time to adjust to other medium to large dogs in her new home but should not be around any small dogs, under any circumstances nor should she ever be allowed around small children!!!!! If you feel like you could be able to provide the perfect home for this tortured soul and help her to move on with her life and truly begin anew and experience all the love and compassion a family member deserves, please send an email to 
Mutts2majestyrescue.apps@gmail.com requesting an application! Thank you in advance!

animal.description:
This sweet boy was returned to BDC when his family was deployed overseas. 

All About Blake

Blake is used to being inside with his people and is kenneled when home alone. He enjoys playing and sunbathing in a fenced backyard frequently throughout the day. 

He must be kept on a leash or in a fenced yard when outside because he is easily distracted and will run off. However, he would love to be on a property with lots of land to run if there were no close roads or neighborhood dogs/kids.
Blake loves his daily walks (usually twice a day), especially right after his breakfast and dinner. He will eat breakfast between 6-8am and dinner as early as 4pm.

House Manners
Blake is fully house-trained and will paw at the door to indicate that he needs to ""get busy"" or wants to go outside. 
He is used to being allowed on the living room furniture.
He will bark when anyone comes to the door or approaches the house. When guests visit, he is initially very excited and needs to be on a leash so that he knows not to jump on people...eventually he will settle down.
Blake still has some ""puppy"" in him and will sometimes steal things off counters, tables, and furniture like laundry, paper, kids toys, and anything within reach that might be fun to play with. If he isn't napping or lounging and is left unoccupied in a room he will most likely try to be sneaky and get into some trouble (he always finds the trashcans!). 
	
Obedience/Commands
Blake went through basic obedience training at River Ridge Kennels in Richlands in October 2018. He knows basic commands. He still needs to work on his heel when walking and not jumping on people when he is excited. 

Basic commands:
-Sit: hold pointer finger up and say ""sit""
-Down: use hand in front of his nose to guide him down and say ""down"" 
-""Off""/""no jump""
-""leave it"": anything you want him to leave alone, like laundry, squirrels, 	other dogs, etc.
	
Likes
-walks and runs on a leash
-the beach
-short car rides
-playing fetch inside
-being brushed
-morning bellyrubs (or any time of day)

Dislikes
-having his nails trimmed (only the groomer has been able to do this for him)

Social behavior 
-with people: Generally Blake is friendly and gets excited to meet people (either at home or on walks). 
-with dogs: Aside from not liking small dogs, Blake is unpredictable in whether he will like a dog his size or larger. He gets along well with labs and ""carefree"" dogs. As long as the other dog doesn't show dominance or aggression, Blake is usually friendly.

Overall, Blake is a loyal dog who loves his people. He would do well in a home with a large backyard and an active family (perhaps with teenagers or older).

animal.description:
Amelia is a sweet, 10- year-old female Chihuahua. In her early life, Amelia was mistreated, but she has been able to heal and enjoy her life now. She loves to relax and be held, and likes to try to take charge of everyone in her foster home, earning the nickname of " little boss". Like Annabella, she loves all people, gets along with children, enjoys the company of other dogs, and ignores the cat. Unlike Annabella, Amelia does not like to go for walks. In fact, she will refuse to move. All of Amelia's teeth are missing on one side of her mouth, which results in her cute tongue-out appearance. Amelia has been pad trained, and she does well with it most of the time.

Amelia and Annabella are a bonded pair so must be adopted together. 

The suggested adoption donation for Amelia and Annabella together is $350. We are a 501c3 organization which means that your donation may be TAX DEDUCTIBLE. Your donation goes toward the high cost of veterinary care for our animals in rescue, as well as providing supportive services to animals in homes.

Information about the adoption process: All adoptions require a completed ADOPTION APPLICATION. Once your application is approved, we will put you in touch with the dogs foster to see if you and the pet are a good match. If so, we will arrange a meeting for you and the pet. The adoptions for all of our animals will take place in the Omaha, NE area and must be done by the adoptive family in person. We do not ship or deliver.

Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We always select the right applicant for each dog, based on the dogs needs. If you and the dog are not a good match, we will help you select another dog, or we will keep your approved application on file for 6 months.

To learn about Muddy Paws Second Chance Rescue or donate to our animals, please visit our website at MuddyPawsSecondChanceRescue.com or our Facebook Page.

animal.description:
Annabella is a lively, 10-year old Chihuahua/Rat errier mix with a sweet disposition. She is very attentive and extremely loyal to her family, and she does well with all people, including children. In fact, she considers it her job to be sure no lap is ever empty. She shows no aggression and is great with other dogs and ignores cats. She loves to play with her stuffed toys, especially her loofah dog. With her loud bark, Annabella gives warning of anything unusual going on outside; however, she has lived in an apartment with no complaints. She is learning about crate training, but whines at first unless she can see her people. Annabella is pad trained, but is learning to go outside to potty. She loves being outside enjoying the fresh air and going for walks.

Annabella and Amelia are a bonded pair and must be adopted together.

The suggested adoption donation for Annabella and Amelia together is $350. We are a 501c3 organization which means that your donation may be TAX DEDUCTIBLE. Your donation goes toward the high cost of veterinary care for our animals in rescue, as well as providing supportive services to animals in homes.

Information about the adoption process: All adoptions require a completed ADOPTION APPLICATION. Once your application is approved, we will put you in touch with the dogs foster to see if you and the pet are a good match. If so, we will arrange a meeting for you and the pet. The adoptions for all of our animals will take place in the Omaha, NE area and must be done by the adoptive family in person. We do not ship or deliver.

Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We always select the right applicant for each dog, based on the dogs needs. If you and the dog are not a good match, we will help you select another dog, or we will keep your approved application on file for 6 months.

To learn about Muddy Paws Second Chance Rescue or donate to our animals, please visit our website at MuddyPawsSecondChanceRescue.com or our Facebook Page.
